race.comment: MONTE KATE (2) stalked the leader then went home a shade too well last start in a BM72 for the girls over this course and distance. Drops 3kgs in this tougher race. Still open to improvement at the fourth run of the prep so stick with this mare over her pet journey. RINGAROSA (7) settled midfield and wound up 2.6 lengths behind MONTE KATE here a fortnight ago. Meets her 2.5kgs better and strips fitter after two runs back from a spell. Big chance to close the gap. FINE VINTAGE (1) raced on the speed and narrowly outgunned an in-form mare over 1100m here recently. Won't mind the extra trip and is rock-hard fit four runs into the campaign. SILENTSAR (3) ran an excellent second in fast time when resuming over 1000m at Randwick on Boxing Day. Outclassed in a Magic Millions race last time. Can bounce back in this more suitable contest. SLINKY (4) caught the eye here at this trip last time. McDonald replacing a 3kg claimer is significant.
